definitions.definition: Towards the back or rear ; backwards .
In the rear; a distance behind.
Backward against the mast ; said of the sails when pressed by the wind from the "wrong" (forward) side, or of a ship when its sails are set that way.
definitions.dating_raw: First attested in the late 17 century.

main_definition: ( archaic ) Towards the back or rear ; backwards . [First attested prior to 1150.]
secondary_definitions: ( archaic ) In the rear; a distance behind. [First attested prior to 1150.]

( nautical ) Backward against the mast ; said of the sails when pressed by the wind from the "wrong" (forward) side, or of a ship when its sails are set that way. [First attested in the late 17 century.]
